WEBVTT

00:04.395 --> 00:04.613
.

00:04.656 --> 00:06.658
- Deputy Commissioner Hill?

00:06.702 --> 00:08.269
- I came here to shake hands
with the man

00:08.312 --> 00:09.835
that saved those kids' lives.

00:09.879 --> 00:12.621
It makes me very proud
to know it was a woman,

00:12.664 --> 00:15.319
and a woman of color at that.

00:15.363 --> 00:17.669
- Do you have any interest
in spending Friday

00:17.713 --> 00:18.801
skiing at Crystal Mountain?

00:18.844 --> 00:20.324
- That actually sounds
really fun.

00:20.368 --> 00:22.283
- I can't help--thinking,

00:22.326 --> 00:23.675
if I get another bad hit,

00:23.719 --> 00:25.155
it could mean
the end of my career.

00:25.199 --> 00:27.288
- Make an appointment,
and get checked out.

00:27.331 --> 00:29.159
- Friday, after your shift?

00:29.203 --> 00:31.727
If you have plans,
I can handle it solo.

00:31.770 --> 00:33.816
- I'm going with you, Matt.
That's that.

00:33.859 --> 00:36.471
[dramatic music]

00:43.565 --> 00:46.611
- All right,
now just follow my finger.

00:46.655 --> 00:47.612
Great.

00:47.656 --> 00:50.093
And can you discuss with me

00:50.137 --> 00:52.356
the vision issues
that you're having?

00:52.400 --> 00:55.316
- Yeah, it was basically
tunnel vision.

00:55.359 --> 00:57.753
Everything looked
kind of dark and fuzzy

00:57.796 --> 00:59.624
around the edges.

00:59.668 --> 01:01.409
- Okay, I'm gonna do
a strength test, now.

01:01.452 --> 01:04.194
I just want you to push out
towards me,

01:04.238 --> 01:06.327
with your right hand,

01:06.370 --> 01:09.069
extending your elbow.

01:10.374 --> 01:11.723
Great.

01:11.767 --> 01:14.378
Now, same thing with the left.

01:14.422 --> 01:17.381
[tense tones]

01:17.425 --> 01:24.432
♪

01:26.564 --> 01:27.870
- I need to get an MRI.

01:27.913 --> 01:29.872
He said it's possible
the repeat trauma

01:29.915 --> 01:32.266
has left behind
permanent damage.

01:32.309 --> 01:34.355
It could be I'm having
temporal lobe seizures.

01:34.398 --> 01:35.704
- Well, what would that mean?

01:35.747 --> 01:37.401
- They can get progressively
worse,

01:37.445 --> 01:39.447
turn into full body seizures.

01:39.490 --> 01:42.232
I'd have to quit the CFD,
obviously.

01:42.276 --> 01:44.626
- Hey, Matt, slow down.

01:44.669 --> 01:48.717
He said it was possible, not
that it was certain, right?

01:48.760 --> 01:50.414
- Right.

01:50.458 --> 01:52.199
- So, we don't know anything
yet.

01:52.242 --> 01:55.506
We'll get the MRI
and go from there.

01:57.682 --> 01:59.380
It's gonna be okay,

01:59.423 --> 02:02.209
no matter what,
we'll figure it out.

02:08.954 --> 02:10.304
- It could be nothing.

02:10.347 --> 02:12.610
We'll know more after these
tests on Wednesday,

02:12.654 --> 02:13.916
but for the next couple
of shifts,

02:13.959 --> 02:18.268
it's better if I don't
see any action.

02:18.312 --> 02:22.272
I'm fine really.
Just...playing it safe.

02:22.316 --> 02:24.622
- Are you sure?

02:25.928 --> 02:27.712
- I can cover for you on calls.

02:27.756 --> 02:30.237
- And I'm happy to pitch in
around the house,

02:30.280 --> 02:32.282
take some paperwork
off your plate.

02:32.326 --> 02:35.242
I want to stay busy.
- Good.

02:35.285 --> 02:37.548
You just make sure you
take care of yourself.

02:37.592 --> 02:39.811
- Will do.
Thanks, Chief.

02:47.471 --> 02:50.344
[indistinct chatter]

02:51.780 --> 02:53.869
- Hey, Hermann.
- Yeah?

02:53.912 --> 02:57.481
- Would you mind if
Gallo and I take over

02:57.525 --> 02:59.527
a corner of Molly's
on Sunday night?

02:59.570 --> 03:01.398
Reserve some space?
- Uh...

03:01.442 --> 03:02.965
depends for what.

03:03.008 --> 03:04.662
- We meet with a group of young
firefighters once a week.

03:04.706 --> 03:07.622
- Oh, that's a nice idea.
- We swap stories, you know,

03:07.665 --> 03:10.625
share--uh...techniques.

03:10.668 --> 03:12.496
- And drink beer?

03:12.540 --> 03:13.497
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

03:13.541 --> 03:14.672
- Well, then, by all means,

03:14.716 --> 03:18.328
bring your young friends
to Molly's.

03:18.372 --> 03:19.329
- Good morning.

03:19.373 --> 03:22.332
- Morning, Chief.
- Hey, Chief.

03:22.376 --> 03:24.595
- I have to call
an audible today.

03:24.639 --> 03:26.815
Due to medical concerns,
Captain Casey

03:26.858 --> 03:29.948
is gonna have to take
the next two shifts out.

03:32.299 --> 03:35.519
I'll be accompanying truck 81,
calling the shots.

03:35.563 --> 03:38.043
Mouch, take the first seat.

03:38.087 --> 03:39.915
- Sure thing, Chief.

03:39.958 --> 03:41.699
- Okay, couple of other
announcements--

03:41.743 --> 03:43.919
[alarm sounds]

03:43.962 --> 03:47.357
- Engine 51, truck 81,
ambulance 61,

03:47.401 --> 03:51.361
structure fire,
26th and Austin.

03:51.405 --> 03:54.669
[dramatic music]

03:54.712 --> 03:57.411
[sirens wailing]

04:11.076 --> 04:12.730
- Save my store,
please just save my store.

04:12.774 --> 04:13.905
- We're on it, sir,

04:13.949 --> 04:16.038
let these ladies
check you out, okay?

04:16.081 --> 04:17.953
[indistinct commands]
- Got it.

04:19.650 --> 04:20.912
- Kidd,

04:20.956 --> 04:22.523
size it up!

04:22.566 --> 04:23.741
- Fires on one,

04:23.785 --> 04:24.960
heavy smoke on two.

04:25.003 --> 04:26.570
Fire's not
in the structure yet,

04:26.614 --> 04:28.442
but looks like there's plenty
fuel in there.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.791
- 51, lead out.

04:29.834 --> 04:32.707
First floor, Mouch, Gallo,
primary search on one.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.974
- Charge your line!

04:39.017 --> 04:40.628
- All right, let's go.

04:43.631 --> 04:46.286
[exploding sounds]

04:50.507 --> 04:53.467
- We got balloons
exploding in here, Chief.

05:04.434 --> 05:04.869
.

05:04.913 --> 05:07.002
[booming explosions]

05:07.045 --> 05:08.960
[yells indistinct command]

05:10.266 --> 05:12.442
- Fire department, call out!

05:12.486 --> 05:14.401
- Fire department.
Call out!

05:15.402 --> 05:17.360
- Help!

05:17.404 --> 05:18.927
- Go.
- Got it.

05:22.365 --> 05:23.453
- Help!

05:23.497 --> 05:25.412
My daughter,
I can't find her.

05:25.455 --> 05:27.022
Addie!

05:27.065 --> 05:29.851
- We'll--we'll get her.
You gotta go, come on.

05:34.551 --> 05:36.379
- Hey, I'm gonna go
check that out.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.381
You keep going.
- Copy.

05:41.602 --> 05:44.126
Hey, come with me.
Come on with me.

05:44.169 --> 05:46.563
- Upstairs, my neighbor,
she's unconscious, hurry!

05:46.607 --> 05:49.174
- Wait--get back here!

05:51.307 --> 05:53.091
Hey!

05:57.095 --> 05:58.532
- You have a bail-out rope?

05:58.575 --> 06:00.185
- Yeah, of course.

06:00.229 --> 06:02.536
- Great, then I don't
need this.

06:02.579 --> 06:05.539
[tense music]

06:05.582 --> 06:06.888
- [coughing]

06:06.931 --> 06:09.151
- Chief, her daughter's
still inside.

06:09.194 --> 06:10.326
- She was looking around,

06:10.370 --> 06:12.241
I couldn't find her,
she's only six.

06:12.284 --> 06:13.547
- Attention everyone--
- Addie!

06:13.590 --> 06:16.419
We have a missing girl inside,
six years old,

06:16.463 --> 06:18.508
location unknown.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.164
- There she is.
[coughing, wheezing]

06:24.296 --> 06:26.386
Front stairwell's
fully involved.

06:26.429 --> 06:29.084
Only clear way out
is the window.

06:30.477 --> 06:31.913
- All right.

06:36.178 --> 06:39.137
- Hey, I need a ladder
to a second floor window.

06:39.181 --> 06:41.009
B-side, center.

06:41.052 --> 06:42.880
I got two civilians coming out.

06:42.924 --> 06:45.274
One male, one female,
unconscious.

06:45.317 --> 06:46.971
- Copy that, Herrmann.

06:47.015 --> 06:48.582
- How is she?
- She needs oxygen.

06:48.625 --> 06:51.106
We'd get her down faster
with a hasty harness.

06:56.067 --> 06:58.243
- You a firefighter?

06:58.287 --> 07:00.028
- Not anymore.

07:02.987 --> 07:04.032
- Let's do this.

07:04.075 --> 07:05.381
- [grunts]

07:08.558 --> 07:10.342
- Whoa, whoa, hang on.

07:10.386 --> 07:12.301
Wait!

07:12.344 --> 07:15.347
[suspenseful music]

07:15.391 --> 07:21.963
♪

07:22.006 --> 07:23.530
- Okay, lift.

07:26.010 --> 07:27.534
- Hold up.

07:41.548 --> 07:44.028
- Fire Department, call out!

07:44.072 --> 07:45.682
- She was just running around
the store,

07:45.726 --> 07:47.162
looking at all the piñatas.

07:47.205 --> 07:49.077
- Your heart rate's elevated,
so just try to relax.

07:49.120 --> 07:52.036
- And these balloons
hit a light or something,

07:52.080 --> 07:54.561
and just burst into flames.

07:55.300 --> 07:58.652
- Hey you, what do you put
in your balloons?

07:58.695 --> 08:00.523
- Helium is really expensive,

08:00.567 --> 08:03.526
and acetylene works
just the same, so...

08:03.570 --> 08:05.267
- Heads up,

08:05.310 --> 08:07.225
flammable gas stored on site.

08:07.269 --> 08:09.227
Let's hurry it up.
Mouch, report.

08:09.271 --> 08:10.577
- No sight of the girl yet.

08:10.620 --> 08:13.580
- Okay,
coming in to help you look.

08:13.623 --> 08:16.539
- Negative, Chief,
do not come here.

08:16.583 --> 08:18.498
We need to evacuate right now.

08:19.586 --> 08:22.066
- Emergency, emergency,

08:22.110 --> 08:25.026
evacuate now,
we are going defensive.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.464
- [sob]

08:34.601 --> 08:36.690
- Mouch, report,
what's your status?

08:36.733 --> 08:40.084
- [whimpering]

08:40.128 --> 08:41.433
- There you are.

08:42.696 --> 08:44.524
Come on, I got you.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.483
- Mouch, report!

08:55.796 --> 08:57.101
- Mouch, report!

09:01.279 --> 09:03.238
- Here he comes.

09:16.033 --> 09:18.340
- You okay?
- Yeah.

09:20.124 --> 09:21.299
- Whew.

09:21.343 --> 09:23.519
- You good?
- We're all right, Chief.

09:28.045 --> 09:29.656
She's okay.
- Ohh!

09:29.699 --> 09:32.310
- She's okay.
- Mommy!

09:43.844 --> 09:47.195
- Mouch, that was--I mean,

09:47.238 --> 09:48.631
Wow.

09:48.675 --> 09:49.632
You okay?

09:49.676 --> 09:50.807
- [coughs]

09:50.851 --> 09:52.026
Worst party ever.

09:52.069 --> 09:53.593
- Hey,

09:53.636 --> 09:55.072
it was a beautiful save.

09:55.116 --> 09:56.596
But I--

09:56.639 --> 09:59.033
you had to go and steal
my thunder, huh?

09:59.076 --> 10:01.644
I pulled off this
pretty sweet rope rescue,

10:01.688 --> 10:03.341
me and this kid,

10:03.385 --> 10:05.822
some kind of natural born
firefighter.

10:05.866 --> 10:07.607
You guys gotta meet him.

10:07.650 --> 10:09.609
Uh...huh.

10:11.393 --> 10:14.048
Where'd he go?

10:23.884 --> 10:27.148
- Yo, you guys missed
the Mouch save of the century.

10:27.191 --> 10:29.106
- He was like...

10:29.150 --> 10:31.369
Chief, don't come in,
it's too hot.

10:31.413 --> 10:33.633
But then, he bursts
out of the building,

10:33.676 --> 10:34.851
the little girl in his arms.

10:34.895 --> 10:36.810
- Boom! The building
explodes behind him.

10:36.853 --> 10:40.770
- He falls to a knee,
and he's like arghhh...

10:40.814 --> 10:42.685
- Mouch, that sounds like
it's out of a movie.

10:42.729 --> 10:44.078
- Way to go, Mouch!

10:44.121 --> 10:46.080
- Just doing my job,
but thanks, Cap.

10:46.123 --> 10:47.516
- Sorry I missed it.

10:47.559 --> 10:49.518
- Chief.

10:49.561 --> 10:51.085
We heard a Mouch
was a baller today.

10:51.128 --> 10:52.695
- Certainly was.

10:52.739 --> 10:54.392
- Speaking of baller, Chief,

10:54.436 --> 10:56.568
that is one impressive new
truck you got out there.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.266
- Uh...what're you talking
about?

10:58.309 --> 11:00.224
- The beauty that's parked
in your spot,

11:00.268 --> 11:02.618
that's not yours?
- No.

11:02.662 --> 11:05.142
Had to find street parking
three blocks away.

11:05.186 --> 11:07.405
- Ugh. Chief,

11:07.449 --> 11:09.581
everybody in this neighborhood
knows that that is your spot.

11:09.625 --> 11:12.236
- Yeah, it is the sacred
duty of every Chicagoan

11:12.280 --> 11:13.803
to respect dibs.
- Mm-hmm.

11:13.847 --> 11:15.675
- It's the city's curb.

11:15.718 --> 11:17.677
He has a right to park there
if he gets there first.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.504
- Oh, no, Chief.

11:19.548 --> 11:21.463
You gotta get angry about this.
- I do?

11:21.506 --> 11:22.551
- You should leave
a nasty note.

11:22.594 --> 11:23.813
- Yes.

11:23.857 --> 11:26.250
- No, I don't think I need to
go that far.

11:26.294 --> 11:28.426
- As soon as the truck moves,
we'll put some cones out there

11:28.470 --> 11:29.645
to make sure this doesn't
happen again.

11:29.689 --> 11:31.386
- Cones, uh-huh.

11:31.429 --> 11:34.128
No, dibs calls for something
more substantial.

11:34.171 --> 11:36.434
A woman in my neighborhood
once put a

11:36.478 --> 11:38.698
dining room table right out
on the street.

11:38.741 --> 11:40.743
- Okay, that's a little much.

11:40.787 --> 11:42.353
Look, you are the man.
Hold that spot.

11:42.397 --> 11:44.138
[overlapping chatter]

11:49.578 --> 11:50.927
- Hey, you two.

11:50.971 --> 11:53.451
That guy who helped me
with that rope rescue,

11:53.495 --> 11:56.237
you didn't happen to see him
over at Med, did you?

11:56.280 --> 11:57.673
- Uh, yeah, Mason?
- Yeah.

11:57.717 --> 11:58.848
- Nice guy.

11:58.892 --> 12:00.415
Yeah, he was there
checking on his neighbor.

12:00.458 --> 12:02.460
- Oh, were they close?
- Doesn't seem like it.

12:02.504 --> 12:04.201
More that he just wanted to
make sure she was okay.

12:04.245 --> 12:05.289
- He didn't happen to mention

12:05.333 --> 12:06.508
where he was stationed at,
did he?

12:06.551 --> 12:08.292
- What do you mean?

12:08.336 --> 12:10.164
- He said he used to be
a firefighter.

12:10.207 --> 12:12.644
- No, he didn't say anything
about it.

12:12.688 --> 12:14.603
- You should have seen
this kid trying to

12:14.646 --> 12:16.648
save that lady
without anybody's help.

12:16.692 --> 12:18.520
- Well, he said he was heading
back to his place

12:18.563 --> 12:21.175
to see what he could salvage.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.701
- Hey, Bobby,
round up the guys.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.485
We're gonna
go for a ride in this engine.

12:34.710 --> 12:36.320
- Mason, right?

12:37.582 --> 12:39.759
- Oh, hey.
- Hey.

12:39.802 --> 12:43.240
Christopher Herrmann,
Firehouse 51.

12:43.284 --> 12:44.938
Lucky for us, you were here,

12:44.981 --> 12:48.593
or we might not have gotten to
your neighbor in time.

12:48.637 --> 12:50.465
- Yeah, maybe not.

12:52.641 --> 12:55.383
- So, uh,
where were you stationed?

12:55.426 --> 12:57.515
- Colorado.
- No kidding?

12:57.559 --> 12:59.430
What brought you out here?

12:59.474 --> 13:01.302
- Family.

13:01.345 --> 13:03.695
I have an uncle in Lakeview.

13:03.739 --> 13:06.829
- Mason,

13:06.873 --> 13:09.397
you ever think about applying
with the CFD?

13:11.703 --> 13:13.357
- No.

13:13.401 --> 13:15.707
- You can tell me to mind
my own business,

13:15.751 --> 13:18.275
and I'll hit the road, but--

13:18.319 --> 13:22.976
I have been doing this long
enough to recognize raw talent.

13:23.019 --> 13:26.457
What happened? You got hurt?

13:26.501 --> 13:28.590
Whatever it was,

13:28.633 --> 13:30.810
you're still young enough.

13:30.853 --> 13:32.855
You can always apply
with the CFD.

13:32.899 --> 13:35.989
- No, I can't.

13:36.032 --> 13:38.730
- Why not?

13:38.774 --> 13:41.690
- Because I was a firefighter,
in prison.

13:42.909 --> 13:46.521
And the CFD won't hire felons.

13:51.352 --> 13:53.397
- Hey, Gallo.

13:53.441 --> 13:54.572
- What's up, Captain?

13:54.616 --> 13:57.445
- I wanted to say thanks.

13:57.488 --> 14:00.883
For staying on me
about the headaches.

14:00.927 --> 14:03.973
It's part of what prompted me
to get it all checked out.

14:04.017 --> 14:05.801
- No need to thank me.

14:05.845 --> 14:07.498
I just hope everything
turns out well.

14:07.542 --> 14:09.283
- It will.

14:15.593 --> 14:18.553
[somber music]

14:18.596 --> 14:25.603
♪

14:58.375 --> 14:58.810
.

14:58.854 --> 15:01.509
- So, he went from fighting
fires to washing dishes

15:01.552 --> 15:03.119
at his uncle's restaurant.

15:03.163 --> 15:05.905
- What kind of felony
are we talking about here?

15:05.948 --> 15:10.126
On a scale from tax evasion
to serial killer?

15:10.170 --> 15:12.563
- It sounds like, you know,
he fell in a bad crowd

15:12.607 --> 15:14.522
when he was a teenager.
He stole a car

15:14.565 --> 15:17.046
and he got three years for it.

15:17.090 --> 15:18.918
- Teenagers.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.180
- Yeah, tell me about it,
I know.

15:20.223 --> 15:21.921
I just went through it
with Lee Henry.

15:21.964 --> 15:23.357
- And kept him out of jail.

15:23.400 --> 15:25.228
- There but for
the grace of God.

15:25.272 --> 15:28.188
And I still got
four kids to go.

15:28.231 --> 15:30.277
Hey, there he is.

15:30.320 --> 15:31.974
Mason, come on over, sit.

15:32.018 --> 15:33.802
Meet my pal Mouch.

15:33.845 --> 15:36.544
- Herrmann told me what you did
on that call--impressive.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.372
- Forget it, you were the hero.

15:38.415 --> 15:40.548
Saw it with my own eyes,
incredible save.

15:40.591 --> 15:43.551
- Hell yeah it was,
nice job.

15:43.594 --> 15:46.989
So, hey.
I got a question for you, okay?

15:47.033 --> 15:50.036
You said you were on a hand
crew, setting fire lines.

15:50.079 --> 15:53.822
Where did you learn how to tie
hasty harnesses like that.

15:56.520 --> 15:59.088
- In prison, you have
a lot of down time.

15:59.132 --> 16:01.482
All we did was train.

16:01.525 --> 16:04.180
Getting on that crew saved me
from a lot of messed up stuff.

16:04.224 --> 16:07.009
And, we were out helping
people, which felt good.

16:07.053 --> 16:08.968
- Yeah.

16:09.011 --> 16:12.493
- Anyway,
here's to you guys,

16:12.536 --> 16:15.409
putting your necks on the line
to save screw-ups like me.

16:15.452 --> 16:18.325
- Forget that,
you stood with us.

16:18.368 --> 16:20.414
That means a hell of a lot
around here.

16:25.071 --> 16:27.421
- Hey, so, uh,
Boden put a note on that truck.

16:27.464 --> 16:29.510
- Like Capp said.
Did he blast him?

16:29.553 --> 16:31.033
- Oh, no, he was completely
Boden.

16:31.077 --> 16:32.513
Very polite, very chill.

16:32.556 --> 16:36.125
- We should get to shift early
and mark Chief's spot.

16:36.169 --> 16:37.126
- Who's we?

16:37.170 --> 16:38.301
- Us.

16:38.345 --> 16:40.042
- Or you?

16:40.086 --> 16:41.130
- I'm the planner.

16:41.174 --> 16:43.002
- Oh.
[laughs]

16:43.045 --> 16:44.655
- Let's draw straws.

16:44.699 --> 16:46.135
- Now you're talking.

16:46.179 --> 16:48.268
- This is ridiculous.

16:48.311 --> 16:50.618
- No looking.

16:50.661 --> 16:52.489
Okay.

16:52.533 --> 16:55.014
Short straw...

16:55.057 --> 16:58.495
draws the short straw.

16:58.539 --> 16:59.627
- Fine.

17:04.371 --> 17:06.373
Wait...
[laughter]

17:06.416 --> 17:08.418
Oh, come on.

17:08.462 --> 17:10.029
- You made it too easy.

17:10.072 --> 17:13.510
- I feel terrible--you should
have gone skiing without me.

17:13.554 --> 17:16.209
- No, no way.
You're the fun part.

17:16.252 --> 17:18.689
- Well, I'm sorry again
for cancelling.

17:18.733 --> 17:20.343
I just--I don't want
my friend to

17:20.387 --> 17:22.345
go through this medical
stuff solo.

17:22.389 --> 17:23.520
- I get it.

17:23.564 --> 17:25.479
We can do the trip
another time.

17:25.522 --> 17:28.482
- I'd love to.

17:28.525 --> 17:30.614
And, in the meantime,

17:30.658 --> 17:32.921
I know it's
not exactly a ski vacation,

17:32.964 --> 17:35.358
but there is an omelet
festival this week

17:35.402 --> 17:37.360
at a pop-up place
in Logan Square.

17:37.404 --> 17:39.319
- An omelet festival.

17:39.362 --> 17:41.234
- Oh, yeah, omelets are very
trendy right now.

17:41.277 --> 17:44.193
- Oh, well,
then, obviously, yes.

17:44.237 --> 17:46.108
- [laughs]
Yay.

17:46.152 --> 17:47.414
You won't regret it.

17:47.457 --> 17:50.069
I hope.

17:50.112 --> 17:51.505
- I feel like I haven't
been a good friend.

17:51.548 --> 17:52.723
You've been going through
something and

17:52.767 --> 17:54.203
I should have picked up on it.

17:54.247 --> 17:56.336
- That's on me. I made sure
you didn't pick up on it.

17:56.379 --> 17:58.468
- Why?
You can tell me anything.

17:58.512 --> 18:02.168
You better know that by now.
- Yeah, I do, it's just--

18:02.211 --> 18:05.475
I grew up in a family
full of secrets.

18:05.519 --> 18:09.305
I guess, it's--it's become
a fallback for me,

18:09.349 --> 18:12.221
shutting people out,

18:12.265 --> 18:14.223
when things get too rough--
I'm working on it.

18:14.267 --> 18:16.530
- Good.

18:16.573 --> 18:20.577
You shouldn't be going through
something like this alone.

18:22.188 --> 18:23.667
Actually,

18:23.711 --> 18:26.061
Sylvie found out,

18:26.105 --> 18:29.064
and she's been by my side
every step of the way.

18:29.108 --> 18:32.459
She'll be at the MRI tomorrow.

18:32.502 --> 18:34.765
- Glad to hear.

18:34.809 --> 18:37.768
[emotional music]

18:37.812 --> 18:41.076
♪

18:41.120 --> 18:43.557
- I am on my lunch break.
- Ah, jeez.

18:43.600 --> 18:45.080
That's the warm welcome I get

18:45.124 --> 18:47.213
after I bought all those
Girl Scout Cookies

18:47.256 --> 18:50.129
from your daughter?
- Three boxes.

18:50.172 --> 18:51.434
- I got kids in the game, too.

18:51.478 --> 18:53.262
- What do you need,
Christopher?

18:53.306 --> 18:55.351
- Hey--uh, two minutes
with the Commissioner,

18:55.395 --> 18:56.657
that's all I'm asking.

18:56.700 --> 18:59.268
- He's out of town
for a few weeks.

18:59.312 --> 19:01.183
- Can you at least tell me
who's covering for him?

19:01.227 --> 19:03.272
- Why, what's this about?

19:03.316 --> 19:05.056
- CFD hiring policies.

19:05.100 --> 19:06.536
- Talk to Human Resources.

19:06.580 --> 19:10.018
- Nah, I'm not looking
to pass off a resume.

19:10.061 --> 19:12.368
I need a policy change.

19:12.412 --> 19:14.675
- DC Hill,

19:14.718 --> 19:16.590
but she has a ton on her plate
right now,

19:16.633 --> 19:18.461
so don't get your hopes up.

19:20.463 --> 19:22.683
- Thanks, Sandra.
- Mm-hmm.

19:26.774 --> 19:28.819
- And I made a playlist
for you.

19:28.863 --> 19:30.560
I'm texting it to you now.

19:30.604 --> 19:32.388
Then you can just give it to
the radiology tech,

19:32.432 --> 19:34.173
and he'll pipe it in through
the headphones.

19:34.216 --> 19:35.826
- You didn't have to do that.

19:35.870 --> 19:37.393
- Uh, don't thank me yet.

19:37.437 --> 19:40.179
It's mostly smooth jazz
and a couple of

19:40.222 --> 19:42.616
Taylor Swift slow jams
thrown in.

19:42.659 --> 19:44.357
I read you're not supposed
to listen to

19:44.400 --> 19:46.141
anything too stimulating.
- Thanks.

19:48.317 --> 19:50.493
- Matt Casey?

19:50.537 --> 19:53.192
- That's me.

19:53.235 --> 19:54.802
- I'll be here.

19:54.845 --> 19:56.499
Have fun?

19:58.371 --> 20:00.808
- I'll do my best.

20:00.851 --> 20:05.334
[uneasy music]

20:05.378 --> 20:12.298
♪

20:12.341 --> 20:16.302
- You ready?

20:16.345 --> 20:18.086
- Yep.

20:18.129 --> 20:19.305
- Great,

20:19.348 --> 20:21.220
I'll start your playlist.

20:39.629 --> 20:39.847
.

20:39.890 --> 20:41.979
- What's he doing?

20:42.023 --> 20:45.722
- Marking Boden's spot.

20:45.766 --> 20:47.246
- Is that my old recliner?

20:47.289 --> 20:50.510
I thought they took it to
the Salvation Army years ago.

20:50.553 --> 20:52.773
Or was I supposed to?

20:54.688 --> 20:57.081
Should we help?
- He drew the short straw.

21:02.696 --> 21:04.698
- Kidd, hey.

21:07.353 --> 21:10.181
Casey get his head examined?
- Yeah.

21:10.225 --> 21:12.575
Won't get the results
for a couple days, though.

21:12.619 --> 21:14.751
- Okay, um...
listen, I, uh,

21:14.795 --> 21:17.014
I gotta ask you a favor,
and it's kind of a big one.

21:17.058 --> 21:18.407
- Okay.

21:18.451 --> 21:21.541
- I need a meeting with
Deputy Commissioner Hill.

21:21.584 --> 21:24.761
- What makes you think that
I got that kind of juice?

21:24.805 --> 21:26.850
- You've been waving her card
around for weeks,

21:26.894 --> 21:29.679
bragging about my best new
friend at headquarters...

21:29.723 --> 21:31.855
- I have not.

21:31.899 --> 21:33.248
Okay, maybe for a few days.

21:33.292 --> 21:35.206
But then I taped it up in
my locker for safekeeping.

21:35.250 --> 21:37.121
- I've been calling
and emailing,

21:37.165 --> 21:39.123
and I cannot get a response.

21:41.691 --> 21:44.259
- What do you need to talk
to her about?

21:46.000 --> 21:49.351
- No wonder Boden was happy
to jump in the action.

21:49.395 --> 21:51.788
This paperwork is mind numbing.

21:51.832 --> 21:53.964
- You'll be back out there
soon.

21:54.008 --> 21:56.140
- Maybe.

21:56.184 --> 21:58.360
When a doctor says
24 to 48 hours

21:58.404 --> 22:00.319
until they call you in
for results,

22:00.362 --> 22:03.060
we should assume 72, right?

22:03.104 --> 22:05.019
- Whenever it is,
you let me know asap.

22:05.062 --> 22:08.065
That's the deal.

22:08.109 --> 22:10.633
Okay, so,

22:10.677 --> 22:14.028
how terrible was the playlist?

22:14.071 --> 22:15.725
You can be honest.

22:15.769 --> 22:18.685
- It was great.

22:18.728 --> 22:21.165
It was definitely
a distraction...

22:22.297 --> 22:24.081
It was horrible.

22:24.125 --> 22:26.345
- [laughs]

22:26.388 --> 22:28.738
- Hey, Brett, you left your
phone on the table.

22:28.782 --> 22:30.697
It kept buzzing, we couldn't
help but see, um--

22:30.740 --> 22:32.655
you missed one call from your
dad, one from Grainger,

22:32.699 --> 22:36.006
and two from something
called Celebrate Omelets.

22:36.050 --> 22:40.620
- Oh, no, I forgot to confirm
those reservations--damn.

22:44.188 --> 22:45.364
- [exhales]

22:48.758 --> 22:50.194
- Yo.

22:50.238 --> 22:52.066
Did you see we're up to
15 RSVP's for Sunday night?

22:52.109 --> 22:54.198
- Yeah, it's awesome.
- Awesome, but--

22:54.242 --> 22:55.852
it's gonna feel like just
another night of boozing,

22:55.896 --> 22:58.768
unless we come up with
an agenda for the meeting.

22:58.812 --> 23:01.902
- Okay, like...

23:01.945 --> 23:04.165
- I don't know, um...

23:06.080 --> 23:07.211
Maybe a guest speaker.

23:07.255 --> 23:09.083
- Ooh, guest speaker.

23:09.126 --> 23:12.652
I like that, someone who's got
wisdom to impart.

23:12.695 --> 23:15.698
- You want The Bullet.

23:15.742 --> 23:17.352
Mike "The Bullet" Thompson,

23:17.396 --> 23:20.311
a true legend of the CFD.

23:20.355 --> 23:22.226
- He's the one who went back
into that housefire collapse

23:22.270 --> 23:23.793
to save an infant,
a while back.

23:23.837 --> 23:27.449
- 1993, put him on the front
page of the "Tribune."

23:27.493 --> 23:30.452
He's retired now, goes around
the country giving talks.

23:30.496 --> 23:32.846
I'll track him down, see if
he'll meet with your group.

23:32.889 --> 23:34.935
- Wha--Mouch, you don't
have to do that.

23:34.978 --> 23:36.980
- I'm happy to,
I worked with him for a while.

23:37.024 --> 23:38.155
You'll love him.

23:38.199 --> 23:40.767
- Why is the damn coffee pot
empty?

23:40.810 --> 23:42.246
- You doing okay, Chief?

23:42.290 --> 23:44.161
- That truck is in my spot
again.

23:44.205 --> 23:46.816
Ignored my note completely.
Had to go park on Wisconsin.

23:46.860 --> 23:48.992
- Like I said,
you gotta get angry.

23:49.036 --> 23:50.820
- Wait...

23:50.864 --> 23:52.996
he's in your spot?

23:53.040 --> 23:55.477
I put a recliner out there,
that's--

23:55.521 --> 23:57.044
that's supposed to be dibs,
Chief.

23:57.087 --> 24:04.094
♪

24:06.401 --> 24:08.882
- I have never seen him
like this.

24:08.925 --> 24:11.275
- Yeah, Cruz got him really
worked up.

24:15.932 --> 24:18.065
- Uh...
what's your note say, Chief?

24:18.108 --> 24:20.154
- I tried the polite way.

24:20.197 --> 24:23.070
Now I'm gonna use
some colorful language.

24:23.113 --> 24:24.854
Let this thief know,
in no uncertain terms,

24:24.898 --> 24:27.117
he cannot park here again.

24:27.161 --> 24:29.163
- Are you sure?

24:29.206 --> 24:32.732
- You notify me
if he shows himself.

24:36.823 --> 24:40.522
- That genie is not
going back in the bottle.

24:40.566 --> 24:43.438
- I mean, it's not like I don't
want to help Herrmann,

24:43.482 --> 24:47.877
but first, is it even possible?
I mean,

24:47.921 --> 24:49.836
the CFD has a long-standing
policy against

24:49.879 --> 24:52.403
hiring anyone
with a felony conviction.

24:52.447 --> 24:54.884
- Even certain misdemeanors.
- Mm-hmm.

24:54.928 --> 24:56.886
- Second, is it fair?

24:56.930 --> 25:00.542
With so many deserving
candidates already in line,

25:00.586 --> 25:02.762
who don't have a rap sheet,

25:02.805 --> 25:05.068
why shouldn't they get
special treatment?

25:05.112 --> 25:06.069
- That's valid.

25:06.113 --> 25:07.506
- And third...

25:11.292 --> 25:13.468
I, uh, I don't have
a third yet,

25:13.512 --> 25:15.252
but, jump in if you do.

25:15.296 --> 25:17.254
- [laughs]
Listen,

25:17.298 --> 25:19.779
I did tons of dumb stuff
as a teenager,

25:19.822 --> 25:21.345
just didn't get caught.

25:21.389 --> 25:23.217
- I was no angel either.

25:23.260 --> 25:27.090
- And you know,
it's a long shot.

25:27.134 --> 25:31.268
The only question is,
is it a shot worth taking?

25:31.312 --> 25:32.792
- I don't even know the guy.

25:32.835 --> 25:34.010
- Herrmann does.

25:34.054 --> 25:37.274
- Well, they just met like
three days ago.

25:37.318 --> 25:38.972
- Yeah, but--

25:39.015 --> 25:40.060
when was the last time
you saw Herrmann

25:40.103 --> 25:42.802
go to bat for someone
like this?

25:49.504 --> 25:51.593
- Did Dr. Carmen call?

25:51.637 --> 25:53.813
- No, but--

25:53.856 --> 25:55.815
when he does, I was thinking,

25:55.858 --> 25:58.948
it's better if I get
the results alone.

25:58.992 --> 26:01.821
- Oh, okay, why?

26:01.864 --> 26:05.215
- I've been making too big
a deal out of all this.

26:05.259 --> 26:09.524
Honestly, no matter what
the results are, I'm fine.

26:09.568 --> 26:12.614
And you tagging along on every
visit, it's silly.

26:12.658 --> 26:15.269
[alarm sounds]

26:15.312 --> 26:17.967
- Squad 3, ambulance 61,
person trapped,

26:18.011 --> 26:20.535
462 North Clark Avenue.

26:33.504 --> 26:35.332
- Fire department.

26:35.376 --> 26:36.856
- Over here, hurry.

26:36.899 --> 26:39.859
[suspenseful music]

26:39.902 --> 26:46.909
♪

26:50.696 --> 26:53.046
.

26:53.089 --> 26:55.614
- What's your name?
- Amber.

26:55.657 --> 26:56.919
This stupid thing jammed up,

26:56.963 --> 26:58.878
I was just trying to pull
the ball out and--

26:58.921 --> 27:00.923
God, why did I have to use
my dominant hand?

27:00.967 --> 27:03.926
- Hang in there Amber,
they're gonna get you free.

27:03.970 --> 27:06.625
- How bad is it?
I can't really feel anything.

27:06.668 --> 27:08.757
- We can't see yet.

27:08.801 --> 27:12.456
- I start Notre Dame in the
fall to play Division One.

27:12.500 --> 27:14.110
I don't
have time for an injury.

27:14.154 --> 27:15.677
- All right, Cruz, grab a side.

27:15.721 --> 27:16.983
- Yep.

27:20.073 --> 27:21.857
- Am I gonna need stitches?

27:21.901 --> 27:23.511
- No, you've got
a compound fracture.

27:23.554 --> 27:24.947
- What?

27:24.991 --> 27:26.340
Oh, my God.

27:26.383 --> 27:28.385
- I'll get some gauze
and a splint.

27:28.429 --> 27:30.518
- Hold tight, okay?
This might hurt a little.

27:33.956 --> 27:35.654
- Clear.

27:39.745 --> 27:40.876
- [winces]
Ow...

27:40.920 --> 27:43.792
- All right, all right.
Behind you.

27:43.836 --> 27:45.925
Take a seat.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.709
You are tough as hell, Amber.

27:47.753 --> 27:49.668
You're gonna heal up
in no time.

27:49.711 --> 27:51.234
- I hope so.

27:51.278 --> 27:53.933
Because if I can't play tennis,
I might as well be dead.

27:53.976 --> 27:56.500
It's my whole life.

27:56.544 --> 27:59.852
[cries]

27:59.895 --> 28:01.505
- Yo, anything yet?

28:01.549 --> 28:03.551
- Nah, truck's still there.

28:03.594 --> 28:05.640
- Bolden's note?
- Hasn't been touched.

28:05.684 --> 28:07.816
- All right, well,
I'll take over watching

28:07.860 --> 28:09.644
if someone will bring me
a sandwich.

28:09.688 --> 28:11.124
- You sure?
- I want to see what happens

28:11.167 --> 28:13.735
when Bolden
sets eyes on this guy.

28:14.867 --> 28:17.130
[indistinct chatter]

28:21.569 --> 28:23.397
- Hey, Herrmann.

28:25.573 --> 28:27.401
I've been thinking about
that favor you asked.

28:27.444 --> 28:28.750
- Yeah?

28:28.794 --> 28:31.492
- And I put in a call to
Deputy Commissioner Hill.

28:31.535 --> 28:34.016
- You got me a meeting?
- I got us one.

28:34.060 --> 28:36.149
But she's squeezing it in,
so we might have

28:36.192 --> 28:38.760
five, ten minutes tops.

28:38.804 --> 28:41.023
- This is incredible.
- I do have one condition.

28:41.067 --> 28:42.721
- Anything, name it.

28:42.764 --> 28:45.462
- We write out what
we want to say,

28:45.506 --> 28:46.768
and we rehearse it--like we're

28:46.812 --> 28:49.205
doing a show
at the Steppenwolf.

28:49.249 --> 28:50.816
- No problem, yeah.
- All right?

28:50.859 --> 28:54.210
No going off script,
no ad-libbing,

28:54.254 --> 28:57.474
we dial it in and
leave no room for error.

28:57.518 --> 29:00.477
I need to make a good
impression.

29:00.521 --> 29:02.741
- Let's start writing.

29:06.135 --> 29:08.181
- Couldn't find a number for
Mike Thompson yet,

29:08.224 --> 29:10.661
but I talked to his best bud
Denny Blasko--

29:10.705 --> 29:13.534
- Actually, Mouch,
we don't need Mike Thompson.

29:13.577 --> 29:14.970
- You don't?
- No.

29:15.014 --> 29:17.668
We found someone better.
- Better than the Bullet?

29:17.712 --> 29:19.583
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

29:21.281 --> 29:22.238
- What does this mean?

29:22.282 --> 29:25.067
- It means you, Mouch.

29:25.111 --> 29:27.809
- Me?
- Yeah.

29:27.853 --> 29:29.811
I want our group to get
a little taste of

29:29.855 --> 29:31.465
everything I've learned
from you.

29:31.508 --> 29:33.728
From the things
you said to me when

29:33.772 --> 29:35.774
I was locked up on
that stairwell,

29:35.817 --> 29:38.080
to the skills I learned
watching you on every call.

29:38.124 --> 29:40.517
- And, how you kicked
epic amounts of ass

29:40.561 --> 29:41.910
on that party store fire.

29:41.954 --> 29:44.130
- You're the guy
we want to hear from.

29:46.785 --> 29:48.961
- I'm, uh...

29:49.004 --> 29:51.572
let's, uh

29:51.615 --> 29:54.227
let me, uh, let me just
check my schedule.

29:54.270 --> 29:55.228
Make sure I'm free.

29:55.271 --> 29:59.754
[sentimental music]

29:59.798 --> 30:01.800
- Have you guys seen Casey?

30:01.843 --> 30:03.192
- Yeah, he's in his quarters,
I think.

30:03.236 --> 30:04.803
- Thank you.

30:06.674 --> 30:09.068
I'm coming with you
to hear the results.

30:09.111 --> 30:10.983
- Sylvie.
- No, I know firefighting

30:11.026 --> 30:13.681
is your whole life
and you're scared as hell,

30:13.724 --> 30:16.815
but so am I,
and we can be scared together.

30:16.858 --> 30:19.774
- You have your own life to
deal with, I was being selfish.

30:19.818 --> 30:21.863
- Matt Casey,
don't argue with me.

30:21.907 --> 30:25.171
Just call me when you hear
from Carmen, or else.

30:30.916 --> 30:32.961
- I think I'm having
stage fright.

30:33.005 --> 30:37.139
- Maybe, I should do
all the talking.

30:37.183 --> 30:39.054
- Here it is.
[excited laugh]

30:39.098 --> 30:40.273
All right--[ahem].

30:40.316 --> 30:42.666
"Thank you for having us"--

30:42.710 --> 30:47.236
"thank--thank--thank you",

30:47.280 --> 30:50.674
"thank you for having us"--
- Listen, hey,

30:50.718 --> 30:53.677
forget the script, just speak
from your heart.

30:53.721 --> 30:55.854
That's something
you're always good at.

30:57.856 --> 31:00.075
- Commissioner Hill
is ready for you.

31:02.034 --> 31:05.254
- Hm, Stella Kidd
from Firehouse 51.

31:05.298 --> 31:07.953
When I said call anytime,
you didn't hesitate.

31:07.996 --> 31:10.869
- We so appreciate
you meeting with us--

31:10.912 --> 31:12.783
I mean, we know
how busy you are.

31:12.827 --> 31:15.264
- Lieutenant Christopher
Herrmann, Engine 51.

31:15.308 --> 31:18.877
Thank you so much for taking
the time to meet with us.

31:18.920 --> 31:20.704
- Well, I hate to be rude,
but I have to be in

31:20.748 --> 31:22.097
Bridgeport in half an hour,

31:22.141 --> 31:24.883
so why don't you give me
the CliffsNotes version of

31:24.926 --> 31:26.319
whatever brings you here.

31:26.362 --> 31:28.712
- Uh, well, to get right to
the heart of the matter,

31:28.756 --> 31:33.152
we're here about CFD's policy
on hiring felons.

31:33.195 --> 31:37.286
Now, there is this inmate
firefighter from Colorado--

31:37.330 --> 31:39.027
- I'm gonna stop you
right there.

31:39.071 --> 31:41.769
Are you trying to get
some kind of exemption?

31:41.812 --> 31:45.860
- Not exactly, I mean--well,
sort of, but I mean--

31:45.904 --> 31:48.732
We're hoping that policy
can change.

31:48.776 --> 31:52.040
- Or, the exemption,
if that's an option--

31:52.084 --> 31:54.825
- It's not, and to be
perfectly blunt,

31:54.869 --> 31:58.177
a policy change like that will
never get the support it needs.

31:58.220 --> 31:59.918
Not around here.

31:59.961 --> 32:01.702
- Maybe if you knew
more about him.

32:01.745 --> 32:03.704
- Unfortunately, we can't set
that precedent,

32:03.747 --> 32:05.706
or it could open us up
to lawsuits.

32:05.749 --> 32:08.230
- Commissioner, respectfully,

32:08.274 --> 32:10.885
you and I both had to fight

32:10.929 --> 32:13.061
to get our foot
in the CFD's door.

32:13.105 --> 32:15.803
And we can continue to fight

32:15.846 --> 32:18.371
our way up the ladder
to prove we belong.

32:18.414 --> 32:20.982
This young man isn't perfect.

32:21.026 --> 32:24.943
He stole a car when he was 17,
but he served his time.

32:24.986 --> 32:27.423
And he put his life on the line
fighting wildfires,

32:27.467 --> 32:31.950
for 80 cents an hour and some
time knocked off his sentence.

32:31.993 --> 32:33.777
We might him on a call,

32:33.821 --> 32:35.997
where he helped saved
the life of a woman

32:36.041 --> 32:38.260
when he could have
run out the door.

32:38.304 --> 32:41.002
He has CFD material
written all over him,

32:41.046 --> 32:42.786
and he can't even apply.

32:42.830 --> 32:45.267
We just want to give him
a fair shot.

32:50.316 --> 32:54.973
- I appreciate your passion,
truly, I do.

32:55.016 --> 32:58.759
But the CFD is an elite group
of men and women.

32:58.802 --> 33:02.110
We're exclusionary on purpose.

33:02.154 --> 33:04.678
Some people can't be
firefighters,

33:04.721 --> 33:07.376
no matter how bad they want it.

33:18.735 --> 33:19.127
.

33:19.171 --> 33:21.086
- Hello?

33:26.482 --> 33:28.310
Wow, uh--

33:28.354 --> 33:29.877
thank you.

33:29.920 --> 33:32.227
That would be amazing, I--

33:32.271 --> 33:34.751
I'm sure he'd be thrilled.

33:34.795 --> 33:37.232
Yes, of course.

33:37.276 --> 33:39.669
I will put them in touch.

33:39.713 --> 33:41.497
Mm-hmm.

33:41.541 --> 33:43.369
- Hey, Chief,

33:43.412 --> 33:46.415
Chief, he's coming back!

33:46.459 --> 33:48.591
The truck guy.

33:51.638 --> 33:53.379
- Hey!

33:53.422 --> 33:59.950
Are you the jerk that ignores
a note outside of a firehouse?

33:59.994 --> 34:03.476
I wrote a really polite
note to try and get--

34:04.433 --> 34:06.653
I--um...

34:06.696 --> 34:09.351
- I am so sorry about this.

34:09.395 --> 34:12.267
I saw your note the other day,
and I meant to come find you,

34:12.311 --> 34:14.400
but I just got so caught up
with Sister Betty.

34:14.443 --> 34:15.749
She's had such a difficult time

34:15.792 --> 34:16.837
getting into her apartment
since

34:16.880 --> 34:19.579
the ALS got its hooks into her.

34:19.622 --> 34:20.754
- Oh, I, uh...

34:20.797 --> 34:24.584
you know, I can see now,
why you will--

34:24.627 --> 34:25.933
Sister Betty, is it?

34:25.976 --> 34:29.763
You know, you can park here
whenever you need.

34:29.806 --> 34:31.243
Here, let me help--
guys, come and help.

34:31.286 --> 34:33.158
- Oh, no, we got it.

34:33.201 --> 34:34.376
- Um...

34:34.420 --> 34:35.856
Guys, now!

34:39.381 --> 34:41.209
- Oh, wow, gosh.

34:41.253 --> 34:44.256
This is just so kind of you.
You guys are just so nice.

34:44.299 --> 34:47.433
- It's nothing, we're
firefighters, and we, um,

34:47.476 --> 34:50.392
we like to help the public,
you know.

34:50.436 --> 34:52.438
- Well, I really will try not
to park here again.

34:52.481 --> 34:53.787
- Um...

34:53.830 --> 34:55.789
You know, forget anything
I said.

34:55.832 --> 34:58.487
This space is yours,

34:58.531 --> 35:01.969
all day, every day.

35:08.323 --> 35:10.630
- 10 Our Fathers
and 15 Hail Marys

35:10.673 --> 35:14.199
for the filth on that note
before you snatched it away.

35:14.242 --> 35:15.939
- Yes, ma'am--

35:15.983 --> 35:17.680
I mean, sister.

35:17.724 --> 35:20.988
I will...do that.

35:30.824 --> 35:32.782
- Keep the change.

35:32.826 --> 35:34.262
- What's this?

35:34.306 --> 35:35.872
- It's called a challenge coin.

35:35.916 --> 35:38.919
It used to be that it's only
given to station members.

35:38.962 --> 35:40.573
Every house had its own coin.

35:40.616 --> 35:43.793
It's always good to have one
on hand in a firefighter bar,

35:43.837 --> 35:45.795
you know, just in case.

35:45.839 --> 35:48.494
You see, if someone
challenges you

35:48.537 --> 35:50.365
and slaps yours down
on the bar,

35:50.409 --> 35:53.499
and you ain't got your own,
you get stuck buying the round.

35:53.542 --> 35:57.067
- Really?
- Yeah. It's a old tradition.

35:57.111 --> 36:00.723
I hear that it's still a thing
they do in St. Paul.

36:00.767 --> 36:02.638
- I heard that, too.

36:02.682 --> 36:04.510
Yeah.

36:04.553 --> 36:06.164
- Um, I don't follow.

36:06.207 --> 36:09.776
- We got you an interview with
the St. Paul Fire Department.

36:09.819 --> 36:12.300
- To be a firefighter?
- No guarantees.

36:12.344 --> 36:14.694
But it's a foot in the door.

36:14.737 --> 36:16.739
- Wait, what? How?

36:16.783 --> 36:19.394
- Because, Stella Kidd here
is best friends with

36:19.438 --> 36:21.004
the Deputy Commissioner
here in Chicago.

36:21.048 --> 36:23.050
- Not quite, but--

36:23.093 --> 36:24.617
we spoke to her,

36:24.660 --> 36:26.488
and whatever we said
must have landed,

36:26.532 --> 36:30.275
because she reached out
to a friend in St. Paul

36:30.318 --> 36:33.321
who happens to be
the Deputy Chief.

36:33.365 --> 36:36.890
And he wants to meet you.

36:36.933 --> 36:39.545
- I wish we could have helped
you out here,

36:39.588 --> 36:42.417
but CFD, they got some strict
policies...

36:42.461 --> 36:44.985
- Are you kidding?
This is unreal.

36:47.770 --> 36:50.120
I can't believe
you did this for me.

36:50.164 --> 36:52.775
- Hey, that, my friend,
is just a loaner.

36:52.819 --> 36:54.603
Okay?

36:54.647 --> 36:56.301
Until you get your own.

37:00.392 --> 37:02.437
- So, without further ado,

37:02.481 --> 37:05.614
let me turn it over to
my friend and mentor,

37:05.658 --> 37:07.703
Randall McHolland.

37:07.747 --> 37:11.316
[applause]

37:11.359 --> 37:12.621
- Ah, boy.

37:12.665 --> 37:15.102
Look at all these young faces.

37:15.145 --> 37:19.324
I don't have any pearls of
wisdom for you folks,

37:19.367 --> 37:20.803
I just know

37:20.847 --> 37:24.459
that the way you learn to do
this job, the way you

37:24.503 --> 37:28.681
maximize your chances
for survival...

37:29.464 --> 37:30.465
- Hmm,

37:30.509 --> 37:33.468
ooh, what is the tornado
omelet?

37:33.512 --> 37:36.558
- I had no idea omelets
were so popular.

37:36.602 --> 37:38.168
You're really in the know.

37:38.212 --> 37:40.432
- That's me, cutting edge.

37:40.475 --> 37:46.655
[phone rings]

37:46.699 --> 37:48.744
Sorry, I gotta take this.

37:48.788 --> 37:50.006
Hey.

37:50.050 --> 37:51.399
Okay.

37:51.443 --> 37:54.794
Of course, yeah, um...

37:54.837 --> 37:59.059
I can be there in about
20 minutes.

37:59.102 --> 38:00.930
Bye.

38:00.974 --> 38:04.804
Um,
I'm so sorry to do this.

38:04.847 --> 38:07.850
My--my friend just heard that
the doctor has results.

38:07.894 --> 38:09.461
- You warned me
this could happen,

38:09.504 --> 38:11.941
I can't get upset about that.

38:13.595 --> 38:18.383
You left out that the friend
you're helping is Casey.

38:18.426 --> 38:19.906
- Oh, I...

38:19.949 --> 38:21.908
it's really just a--
it's a privacy thing, I mean,

38:21.951 --> 38:24.563
he hasn't told a lot of people,
I feel--

38:24.606 --> 38:27.870
terrible about ruining another
plan, can we reschedule?

38:27.914 --> 38:29.916
Any--any time.

38:32.135 --> 38:34.529
- I don't think
that's such a good idea.

38:36.226 --> 38:37.924
- Why not?

38:37.967 --> 38:42.145
- I think you have some stuff
you need to figure out, Sylvie.

38:42.189 --> 38:45.148
[somber music]

38:45.192 --> 38:52.199
♪

38:59.946 --> 39:01.426
- Sorry, I took so long.

39:01.469 --> 39:03.036
Any word?

39:03.079 --> 39:05.081
- Nothing.

39:05.125 --> 39:07.475
Nurse seemed serious
when I gave her my name.

39:07.519 --> 39:10.043
Brought me right in.

39:12.741 --> 39:14.526
- It could be nothing.

39:17.529 --> 39:19.618
- Sorry to keep you waiting.

39:22.751 --> 39:24.100
Matt,

39:24.144 --> 39:26.102
in the accident
where you hit your head,

39:26.146 --> 39:28.278
which side of your body
did you fall on?

39:28.322 --> 39:30.759
- Uh...

39:30.803 --> 39:32.239
my left.
- Mm-hmm.

39:32.282 --> 39:35.242
And did you have any
shoulder pain afterwards?

39:35.285 --> 39:38.245
- Uh, yeah, but it's mostly
gone.

39:38.288 --> 39:41.553
- Makes sense now.

39:41.596 --> 39:45.078
The weakness on your left
side is most likely due to

39:45.121 --> 39:47.515
the shoulder injury
you're recovering from,

39:47.559 --> 39:50.605
not from an injury
in the brain.

39:50.649 --> 39:53.739
Your MRI is clean.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.218
- Um,

39:55.262 --> 39:58.787
but what about the headaches
and the tunnel vision?

39:58.831 --> 40:01.790
- Most likely caused by
post-concussion migraines.

40:01.834 --> 40:03.488
It's common with a head injury
like yours.

40:03.531 --> 40:05.011
It'll go away on its own.

40:05.054 --> 40:06.491
In the meantime,

40:06.534 --> 40:09.581
we'll get you some migraine
medication to manage it.

40:09.624 --> 40:11.583
- Uh...

40:11.626 --> 40:13.715
so I'm--I'm clear to work?

40:13.759 --> 40:16.109
- Absolutely.

40:16.152 --> 40:17.502
I'll talk to Jenny out front,

40:17.545 --> 40:20.287
and she'll have your
prescription ready for you.

40:20.330 --> 40:22.811
It's always nice
to deliver good news.

40:29.688 --> 40:32.734
- Matt, you're okay.

40:32.778 --> 40:35.345
[hopeful music]

40:35.389 --> 40:39.132
[laughs]

40:39.175 --> 40:46.182
♪

40:59.152 --> 41:01.328
- Time to...
head to Molly's.

41:01.371 --> 41:03.678
- [laughs]

41:03.722 --> 41:05.375
- We got some celebrating
to do.

41:05.419 --> 41:07.552
- I was thinking
the same thing, yes.

41:07.595 --> 41:09.815
- Right.

41:53.249 --> 41:55.904
[wolf howls]
